==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''abbreviatus'', past participle of ''abbreviare''; ''ad'' + ''breviare'' to [[shorten]], from ''brevis'' short. See [[abridge]].

===Pronunciation===
* ([[RP]]) {{IPA|/əˈbriːvieɪt/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|abbreviate|abbreviates|abbreviated|abbreviating}}

#{{transitive}} To make [[briefer]]; to [[shorten]]; to [[abridge]]; to reduce by contraction or [[omission]], especially of words written or spoken.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*It is one thing to ''abbreviate'' by contracting, another by cutting off. — [[Bacon]]
#{{Mathematics}} To [[reduce]] to lower terms, as a [[fraction]].

